{"data":{"wordpressPost":{"title":"Cool thing Thursday: alertify.js","content":"<a href=\"http://fabien-d.github.com/alertify.js/\"><img class=\"alignnone  wp-image-5615\" title=\"alertify.js\" src=\"http://swizec.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/11/alertify.js-1024x232.png\" alt=\"alertify.js\" width=\"620\" height=\"140\" srcset=\"https://swizec.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/11/alertify.js-1024x232.png 1024w, https://swizec.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/11/alertify.js-300x68.png 300w, https://swizec.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/11/alertify.js.png 1038w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></a>\n<p>Sometimes you come across a library so full of promise and amazingness that you have to write about it before even trying it out.</p>\n<p><a href=\"http://fabien-d.github.com/alertify.js/\" target=\"_blank\">Alertify.js</a> is a <a class=\"zem_slink\" title=\"JavaScript library\" href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/JavaScript_library\" rel=\"wikipedia\" target=\"_blank\">javascript library</a> that brings <em>alert()</em> and <em>prompt()</em> into the web world of 2012. No longer will you be forced to use some arcane instruction full of ugly windows and so terribly un-new it sends chills down your spine just thinking about using it.</p>\n<p>Really &#8230; was anyone still using that for anything other than debugging? Besides <s>porn </s>phishing sites I mean.</p>\n<div id=\"attachment_5616\" style=\"width: 452px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><a href=\"http://swizec.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/11/old-alert.png\"><img class=\" wp-image-5616 \" title=\"The old alert()\" src=\"http://swizec.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/11/old-alert.png\" alt=\"The old alert()\" width=\"442\" height=\"295\" srcset=\"https://swizec.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/11/old-alert.png 632w, https://swizec.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/11/old-alert-300x200.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 442px) 100vw, 442px\" /></a><p class=\"wp-caption-text\">The old alert()</p></div>\n<p>The difference between old way and new is realy quite amazing. While a normal alert() creates a whole new window and blocks javascript execution, alertify&#8217;s <a class=\"zem_slink\" title=\"Dialog box\" href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dialog_box\" rel=\"wikipedia\" target=\"_blank\">alert box</a> is a lot easier on the eye, rolls nicely down from the top of the window and most of all <em>is customisable.</em></p>\n<p>Although blocking execution would actually be kind of useful, alertify.js can fake this with careful use of callback soup and apparently manages to do something to at least prevent clicking on the page. So unless you get an event from a timer or a socket, you can rest assured nothing will happen while the alert is displayed.</p>\n<p>It also plays nice with us keyboard maniacs &#8211; you can use the <em>ESC</em> key to make a Prompt or Confirm dialog go away.</p>\n<p>Another feature I really like are the logging facilities. It&#8217;s a log you actually won&#8217;t mind showing to your users! Wonderful.</p>\n<div id=\"attachment_5617\" style=\"width: 641px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><a href=\"http://swizec.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/11/log-messages.png\"><img class=\" wp-image-5617   \" title=\"Log messages\" src=\"http://swizec.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/11/log-messages-1024x235.png\" alt=\"Log messages\" width=\"631\" height=\"145\" srcset=\"https://swizec.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/11/log-messages-1024x235.png 1024w, https://swizec.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/11/log-messages-300x69.png 300w, https://swizec.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/11/log-messages.png 1129w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 631px) 100vw, 631px\" /></a><p class=\"wp-caption-text\">Log messages</p></div>\n<p>Then again, for debugging I will probably still be using <em>console.log</em> and ruining my sites for all <a class=\"zem_slink\" title=\"Internet Explorer\" href=\"http://www.microsoft.com/windows/internet-explorer/\" rel=\"homepage\" target=\"_blank\">Internet Explorer</a> users when I forget to remove debugging lines &#8230; with alertify.js it&#8217;s at least impossible to forget.</p>\n<p>Oh and another cool thing, Fabien Doiron implemented the whole thing without <a class=\"zem_slink\" title=\"JQuery\" href=\"http://jquery.com/\" rel=\"homepage\" target=\"_blank\">jQuery</a>, which I think is just impressive, these days I probably can&#8217;t do anything without jQuery anymore &#8230;</p>\n<h6 class=\"zemanta-related-title\" style=\"font-size: 1em;\">Related articles</h6>\n<ul class=\"zemanta-article-ul zemanta-article-ul-image\" style=\"margin: 0; padding: 0; overflow: hidden;\">\n<li class=\"zemanta-article-ul-li-image zemanta-article-ul-li\" style=\"padding: 0; background: none; list-style: none; display: block; float: left; vertical-align: top; text-align: left; width: 84px; font-size: 11px; margin: 2px 10px 10px 2px;\"><a style=\"box-shadow: 0px 0px 4px #999; padding: 2px; display: block; border-radius: 2px; text-decoration: none;\" href=\"http://blog.studentrnd.org/post/36041434495/tutorial-creating-a-reddit-browser-with-node-js-and\" target=\"_blank\"><img style=\"padding: 0; margin: 0; border: 0; display: block; width: 80px; max-width: 100%;\" src=\"http://i.zemanta.com/noimg_101_80_80.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></a><a style=\"display: block; overflow: hidden; text-decoration: none; line-height: 12pt; height: 80px; padding: 5px 2px 0 2px;\" href=\"http://blog.studentrnd.org/post/36041434495/tutorial-creating-a-reddit-browser-with-node-js-and\" target=\"_blank\">Creating a Reddit Browser with Node.js and Twilio</a></li>\n<li class=\"zemanta-article-ul-li-image zemanta-article-ul-li\" style=\"padding: 0; background: none; list-style: none; display: block; float: left; vertical-align: top; text-align: left; width: 84px; font-size: 11px; margin: 2px 10px 10px 2px;\"><a style=\"box-shadow: 0px 0px 4px #999; padding: 2px; display: block; border-radius: 2px; text-decoration: none;\" href=\"http://magedfar